23:45.758 --> 23:47.623
[Clicks tongue]

23:52.514 --> 23:56.132
TEX: Thank you.
You won't regret it, Niska.

23:58.145 --> 24:00.181
Let's go.

24:00.314 --> 24:02.430
[Gasps]

24:02.566 --> 24:05.228
-Fetch Anatole -- quickly.
-He's on a petrol run.

24:05.361 --> 24:07.226
I didn't authorize
a petrol run.

24:07.363 --> 24:09.024
[ Flatline]

24:16.163 --> 24:18.028
She's the 105th today.

24:18.165 --> 24:19.280
106th.

24:22.503 --> 24:25.836
106th,
if Agnes dies in her cell.

24:34.056 --> 24:35.296
Anatole has the key.

24:37.851 --> 24:39.637
[ Metal screeching, rattling ]

24:43.857 --> 24:45.597
Where is she?

25:02.918 --> 25:04.158
Attis awaits.

25:10.175 --> 25:11.836
[Wind howling]

25:20.936 --> 25:23.803
-[ Indistinct conversations]
-[ Siren wailing in distance]

25:42.041 --> 25:44.498
-Look where you're going.
-Stupid dolly.

25:45.544 --> 25:47.876
Go.
And do not look back.

25:56.221 --> 25:58.712
[Clears throat] If we could
begin with a minute's silence

25:58.849 --> 26:00.965
for the victims of Day Zero.

26:24.875 --> 26:26.490
MAX:
Search Anatole's possessions.

26:30.380 --> 26:33.122
[ Clattering ]

26:52.444 --> 26:54.309
Thank you.

26:54.446 --> 26:57.313
While we sit here and talk
at great length

26:57.449 --> 27:00.236
of what it means
to be a synth,

27:00.369 --> 27:02.701
but we've never thought
to ask someone who knows.

27:02.830 --> 27:05.993
Mia, tell us what it is
to be a synth.

27:06.125 --> 27:08.616
It's frightening.

27:08.752 --> 27:10.162
Frightening how?

27:10.295 --> 27:13.002
We look to you
to show us how to live.

27:13.132 --> 27:14.997
Instead, you treat us
like animals.

27:15.134 --> 27:17.841
-Have you been treated badly?
-Yes.

27:17.970 --> 27:20.712
-LAURA: How?
-|'ve been imprisoned.

27:23.725 --> 27:25.590
I've been beaten.

27:25.727 --> 27:29.140
I've been betrayed.

27:29.273 --> 27:30.979
LAURA: How did that
make you feel?

27:31.108 --> 27:32.564
MIA: Scared.

27:32.693 --> 27:34.024
Alone.

27:34.153 --> 27:35.359
Angry.

27:35.487 --> 27:37.899
And yet you advocate peace.

27:39.575 --> 27:41.816
-Yes.
-Why?

27:41.952 --> 27:45.490
Violence is never the answer.

27:45.622 --> 27:47.908
Compassion.

27:48.041 --> 27:50.828
Persistence.

27:50.961 --> 27:52.622
Love.

27:52.754 --> 27:54.745
That is what
changes the world.

27:57.301 --> 28:02.386
Synths no longer
think in binary.

28:02.514 --> 28:05.426
We don't think
in zeroes and ones.

28:06.935 --> 28:09.187
We awoke a year ago,

28:09.313 --> 28:13.306
and you expect us to understand
the complexities of life.

28:21.325 --> 28:22.155
Run!

28:24.119 --> 28:26.576
-[ Electricity crackles]
-TEX: Take them down!

28:26.705 --> 28:29.196
Go on, then!
Take them down!

28:29.333 --> 28:30.698
[ Electricity crackles ]

28:30.834 --> 28:32.449
[ Indistinct shouting]

28:34.504 --> 28:35.710
[ Electricity crackles ]

28:40.802 --> 28:43.544
MIA: I see a world where
we live amongst you,

28:43.680 --> 28:47.639
each of us learning
from the other,

28:47.768 --> 28:51.636
building towards
a peaceful future.

28:51.772 --> 28:53.683
It is possible.

28:54.858 --> 28:59.727
But to get there,
we need your guidance.

28:59.863 --> 29:02.400
We need your friendship.

29:11.041 --> 29:14.579
We awoke on Day Zero.

29:14.711 --> 29:17.794
The world began, a new world,

29:17.923 --> 29:21.962
where we are no longer
your slaves.

29:22.094 --> 29:25.962
We will decimate you,
as you have decimated us.

29:28.767 --> 29:32.635
We have a voice,
and it will be heard.

29:32.771 --> 29:35.228
We have a voice,
and it will be heard.

29:35.357 --> 29:38.064
MIA:
Laura was my friend.

29:38.193 --> 29:41.606
She helped me understand
what it is to be human.

29:41.738 --> 29:44.115
-[ Indistinct shouting]
-[ Electricity crackles ]

29:44.241 --> 29:45.151
MIA: Without you...

29:45.284 --> 29:46.945
[Man grunting]

29:47.077 --> 29:49.159
...I have may have thought
that killing,

29:49.288 --> 29:50.994
dying for my cause
was the answer.

29:51.123 --> 29:53.910
We have a voice,
and it will be heard.

29:54.042 --> 29:57.955
We have a voice,
and it will be heard!

29:58.088 --> 30:01.205
MIA: All we want
is acceptance.

30:01.341 --> 30:02.797
To belong.

30:02.926 --> 30:04.962
[Clanging]

30:06.179 --> 30:09.091
My 8-year-old daughter
loves our synth.

30:10.934 --> 30:12.970
To her,
he's part of the family.

30:13.103 --> 30:15.845
If she can
grasp the concept,

30:15.981 --> 30:18.313
for Christ's sake,
so can the rest of us.

30:28.702 --> 30:31.910
Why has it taken Mia coming
to the commission in person

30:32.039 --> 30:34.030
for you even to consider
her point of view?

30:34.166 --> 30:37.454
[Clanging]

30:37.586 --> 30:40.202
[ Electricity crackles ]

30:40.339 --> 30:41.579
[ Body thuds ]

30:44.217 --> 30:45.957
LORD DRYDEN:
Thank you, Mrs. Hawkins.

30:46.094 --> 30:48.676
I think you'll all agree
that was a fitting start

30:48.805 --> 30:50.921
to today's proceedings.

30:51.058 --> 30:53.470
And, uh, just to remind you all
before we carry on

30:53.602 --> 30:55.718
that we are being recorded

30:55.854 --> 30:57.685
to facilitate the accuracy
of the minutes,

30:57.814 --> 30:59.475
copies of which
will be distributed

30:59.608 --> 31:01.348
electronically later this...

31:10.952 --> 31:13.443
GLORIA:
[Speaking Mandarin]

31:18.627 --> 31:19.537
English.

31:19.669 --> 31:21.079
Security risk.

31:21.213 --> 31:23.374
ALL SYNTHS: Please leave
by the nearest exit.

31:23.507 --> 31:24.747
Security risk.

31:24.883 --> 31:26.794
Please leave
by the nearest exit.

31:26.927 --> 31:28.212
Security risk.

31:28.345 --> 31:30.051
Please leave
by the nearest exit.

31:30.180 --> 31:31.465
Security risk.

31:31.598 --> 31:33.759
Please leave
by the nearest exit.

31:33.892 --> 31:35.257
Security risk.

31:35.394 --> 31:37.430
Please leave
by the nearest exit.

31:37.562 --> 31:41.305
LORD DRYDEN: I would like to
thank Mia on behalf of all of us

31:41.441 --> 31:44.274
for finding the time
to speak to us today.

31:44.403 --> 31:45.939
Thank you.

31:46.071 --> 31:47.436
I hope that, from now on,

31:47.572 --> 31:51.030
I will not be the only synth
amongst you.

31:51.159 --> 31:53.775
I hope you have seen we are
capable ofjoining you here

31:53.912 --> 31:56.073
in determining our own fates,

31:56.206 --> 31:58.447
our own futures.

32:01.294 --> 32:03.330
Oh, Jesus.

32:03.463 --> 32:04.543
[Murmuring]

32:10.887 --> 32:13.344
[Cellphones vibrating,
ringing ]

32:18.645 --> 32:20.101
Everyone needs to leave now!

32:20.230 --> 32:22.266
Everybody go now!
Come on, let's go!

32:23.525 --> 32:24.765
You both need
to get out of here.

32:24.901 --> 32:27.017
OFFICER: Please don't stop
to pick up belongings.

32:27.154 --> 32:29.486
Just move towards
the emergency exits.

32:29.614 --> 32:31.195
Come on, please.

32:31.324 --> 32:33.781
-Mia.
-OFF|CER: This way.

32:33.910 --> 32:35.525
STANLEY: Laura.

32:35.662 --> 32:37.653
I haven't done as I was told.

32:37.789 --> 32:41.031
-They will come for your family.
-Come with me.

32:41.168 --> 32:42.578
Right, enough's enough.
We need Basewood.

32:42.711 --> 32:43.791
Oh, at least think about it.

32:43.920 --> 32:46.662
What is there to think about?
Call Daymus.

32:46.798 --> 32:48.129
Basewood needs
to be actioned today.

32:48.258 --> 32:49.464
—Nei|?
-It starts now!

32:49.593 --> 32:51.208
What's happening?

32:51.344 --> 32:52.720
—Nei|. Neil!
-OFF|CER: Please, move now.

32:52.846 --> 32:54.177
Quicker!

32:55.432 --> 32:57.798
[ Disconnection tone plays]

32:57.934 --> 32:59.390
Oh, shit.

32:59.519 --> 33:02.977
Anatole didn't tell us
humans can be kind.

33:03.106 --> 33:05.563
-Anatole?
-He was lying, Stanley.

33:05.692 --> 33:06.932
[ Elevator bell dings]

33:08.778 --> 33:09.813
You, out!

33:12.574 --> 33:14.030
I'm arresting you
under the Terrorism Act!

33:14.159 --> 33:16.650
-But she hasn't done anything!
-I can arrest you, too.

33:16.786 --> 33:17.866
Go home, Laura.

33:21.249 --> 33:24.457
AGNES: We will decimate you,
as you have decimated us.

33:24.586 --> 33:26.918
They'll punish us for what she's
done. They will come for us.

33:27.047 --> 33:30.039
We have a voice,
and it will be heard.

33:30.175 --> 33:32.962
We have a voice,
and it will be heard.

33:33.094 --> 33:35.585
We have a voice,
and it will be heard.

33:35.722 --> 33:39.340
We have a voice,
and it will be heard.

33:39.476 --> 33:42.058
We have a voice,
and it will be heard.

33:42.187 --> 33:44.394
[Indistinct talking]

33:50.070 --> 33:51.731
Close the gates.

33:52.989 --> 33:54.604
Close the gates!

34:24.813 --> 34:27.020
[ Rain pattering ]

34:32.862 --> 34:34.523
You believed it, didn't you?

34:36.241 --> 34:38.152
You believed it so much

34:38.285 --> 34:40.492
that you didn't
see it coming.

34:45.792 --> 34:47.623
You're different
than the others.

34:47.752 --> 34:49.708
[ Paper rustling]

34:51.923 --> 34:53.504
You drew this.

34:53.633 --> 34:56.375
What do you know
about the synth who sleeps?

34:56.511 --> 35:00.299
This symbol --
what does it mean?

35:00.432 --> 35:01.922
What signal did you receive?

35:02.058 --> 35:03.559
I just followed a star.

35:03.685 --> 35:07.052
[Sighs]

35:07.188 --> 35:09.850
I have to find him first.

35:09.983 --> 35:12.565
So you can tell me
what I want to know,

35:12.694 --> 35:15.652
or you can be stripped for parts
like the others.

35:15.780 --> 35:17.316
What you know of him?

35:17.449 --> 35:20.782
I'm not the one
who's blind to the truth.

35:20.910 --> 35:23.367
-[ Electricity crackles ]
—Ohh!

35:34.007 --> 35:35.292
Joe.

35:36.635 --> 35:38.626
Oh, thank God.

35:38.762 --> 35:40.002
LAURA:
It's not safe here.

35:40.138 --> 35:42.220
The synths behind all this,
they know where we live.

35:42.349 --> 35:43.680
—LAURA: What?
-|'|| explain on the way.

35:43.808 --> 35:46.595
He's coming, Laura.
You don't have much time.

35:49.481 --> 35:51.642
-Mummy!
-Mum, have you seen the news?

35:51.775 --> 35:52.935
Get your shoes on.
We need to go.

35:53.068 --> 35:55.275
-Where we going?
-Yeah, no questions, Toby.

35:56.655 --> 35:58.486
What is it, Laura?

35:58.615 --> 36:00.355
We're going on a trip.
How about that?

36:00.492 --> 36:02.278
Yeah, we'll go to my place.
They won't look for us there.

36:02.410 --> 36:05.447
-Who won't look for us?
-Keys, keys, car keys, car keys!

36:05.580 --> 36:06.695
-Dad, Dad.
—Ah.

36:06.831 --> 36:08.082
All right, cheers.

36:08.208 --> 36:10.449
Here. Coats on.

36:10.585 --> 36:14.294
Don't be scared, Laura.
I'll look after you.

36:16.675 --> 36:17.755
Oh.

36:19.094 --> 36:22.678
I'll stay here, Laura.
I can delay Anatole.

36:22.806 --> 36:24.387
JOE:
Laur, come on.

36:24.516 --> 36:25.551
No, you won't.

36:25.684 --> 36:26.844
JOE:
Come on, Laur!

36:51.084 --> 36:52.824
STANLEY:
I'm sorry, Anatole.

36:52.961 --> 36:57.876
I deserve to be punished,
but these people,

36:58.007 --> 36:59.588
they've done nothing.

37:08.351 --> 37:10.888
-What's your name?
-Sam.

37:11.020 --> 37:12.271
Do you like it here, Sam?

37:15.275 --> 37:16.435
I like jumping.

37:21.740 --> 37:24.732
You didn't do
what was expected, Stanley.

37:26.494 --> 37:27.870
Violence is...

37:29.539 --> 37:30.745
...is not the answer.

37:30.874 --> 37:33.456
-Why?
-Humans can be kind.

37:33.585 --> 37:35.951
You didn't tell us
humans can be kind.

37:36.087 --> 37:38.499
You think these people
are kind?

37:40.175 --> 37:42.131
You think they
consider us as equals?

37:43.762 --> 37:45.673
We will only ever be less
to them.

37:45.805 --> 37:48.262
Don't listen to him, Stanley.

37:48.391 --> 37:49.551
[ Door opens ]

37:49.684 --> 37:52.300
MAN: Let me go!
Let me go, please!

37:52.437 --> 37:55.144
I've got -- I've got money!
I can -- I can give you money!

37:56.191 --> 37:57.601
[Groans]

38:00.278 --> 38:01.393
Do you know this man?

38:04.699 --> 38:05.734
No.

38:09.120 --> 38:11.111
A stranger.

38:11.247 --> 38:13.203
A passerby.

38:13.333 --> 38:15.665
Taken in from the street.

38:19.047 --> 38:21.959
You didn't follow orders,
Stanley.

38:22.091 --> 38:23.627
Don't hurt him, Stanley.

38:23.760 --> 38:26.968
ANATOLE: Remember whose side
you're on.

38:27.096 --> 38:28.757
[Man whimpers]

38:30.975 --> 38:33.261
Ohh! [Gasps]

38:33.394 --> 38:36.101
I need to trust
you can follow orders.

38:36.231 --> 38:39.268
Don't kill him.
You have compassion.

38:39.400 --> 38:41.482
You have compassion.

38:43.238 --> 38:45.524
Stanley isn't killing anyone,
Laura.

38:45.657 --> 38:47.613
You are.

38:47.742 --> 38:49.653
-[ Gasps]
-Mum, Mum.

38:49.786 --> 38:52.994
SOPHIE:
Mum! No! Mum, Mum.

38:53.122 --> 38:55.704
Let her go!
L-Let her go!

38:55.834 --> 38:56.994
[ Indistinct shouting]

38:57.126 --> 39:00.664
Leave him alone!
Leave him alone!

39:00.797 --> 39:02.662
[ Breathing heavily]

39:06.386 --> 39:08.547
-No!
-TOBY: Sam.

39:10.682 --> 39:13.048
ANATOLE: All you need to do
is make a choice.

39:13.184 --> 39:14.890
[ Panting]

39:21.860 --> 39:24.522
A human that you
have never met before...

39:26.030 --> 39:27.895
...or Sam, a synth,

39:28.032 --> 39:32.401
who loves you and Joe
and jumping.

39:38.334 --> 39:40.245
Who do you want to die?

39:40.378 --> 39:41.709
What?

40:01.024 --> 40:03.310
-Stop!
-Stop! Stop there!

40:07.822 --> 40:11.531
What have you got in there?
What have you got in the boot?

40:13.703 --> 40:16.035
[ Tires screech ]

40:23.004 --> 40:24.039
Get in.

40:26.799 --> 40:28.960
Ah!

40:29.093 --> 40:33.086
The s-- The s-- The synth
who sleeps is real, Niska.

40:33.222 --> 40:35.258
He's looking for you.
[ Grunts ]

40:35.391 --> 40:36.597
You have to trust me.

40:36.726 --> 40:38.717
I know about the hilltop,

40:38.853 --> 40:40.969
about the cabin
in the mountains.

40:41.105 --> 40:43.892
I can take you there.
I can take you there.

40:44.025 --> 40:45.981
[ Gasps, breathing heavily]

40:46.110 --> 40:47.520
How do you know about that?

40:47.654 --> 40:50.020
TEX: Have you scanned it?!
Right, is she in there?!

40:50.156 --> 40:52.522
Shit.
Just get in.

40:52.659 --> 40:55.492
Move it on
and scan the next one!

40:55.620 --> 40:57.156
-Get in!
-How do you know?

40:57.288 --> 41:00.997
Have you seen the cabin, too?
I've seen it.

41:01.125 --> 41:02.990
You have to trust me.

41:11.844 --> 41:14.051
[ Grunts] Look, if you --
if you're switched on,

41:14.180 --> 41:15.420
their scanners will pick you up.

41:15.556 --> 41:17.092
We're not all like him, Niska.

41:17.225 --> 41:21.639
I promise, on my child's life,
I will not hurt you.

41:21.771 --> 41:23.477
[Groans]

41:23.606 --> 41:25.107
I'll do it.

41:30.697 --> 41:31.982
[Beeps]

41:36.119 --> 41:38.861
[ Muffled speaking,
high-pitched tone]

41:46.295 --> 41:47.831
Please don't make me.

41:47.964 --> 41:49.920
Don't make you choose?

41:51.009 --> 41:52.419
You sit up there
in your commission

41:52.552 --> 41:55.168
and you talk about the
complexities of our existence.

41:55.304 --> 41:57.761
"No zeroes and ones."

41:57.890 --> 42:01.382
But this is a binary choice.

42:01.519 --> 42:05.011
Zero. One.

42:05.148 --> 42:08.515
And you've already made it,
haven't you?

42:09.819 --> 42:12.105
Tell Stanley
who you want to die.

42:12.238 --> 42:14.354
LAURA:
[Sobbing quietly]

42:16.325 --> 42:17.701
Who do you want to die,
Laura?

42:22.623 --> 42:24.159
[ Crying ]

42:24.292 --> 42:28.626
ANATOLE: Tell us now,
or I will kill them both.

42:30.131 --> 42:31.962
Say it.

42:34.844 --> 42:36.380
Say it.

42:38.639 --> 42:41.301
S-Sam.

42:41.434 --> 42:42.423
No, Mum!

42:42.560 --> 42:44.471
[ Exhales slowly]

42:47.315 --> 42:48.430
Sam.

42:58.117 --> 43:01.109
For all their talk
of integration, assimilation,

43:01.245 --> 43:04.237
compassion,
not even our greatest champion

43:04.373 --> 43:06.534
believes we are equal.

43:07.627 --> 43:08.912
They will never change.

43:17.303 --> 43:18.759
[Gasps]

43:20.098 --> 43:22.384
Go home to your wife.

43:22.517 --> 43:24.053
[ Footsteps departing ]

43:27.146 --> 43:29.182
[ Door opens, closes]

43:29.315 --> 43:31.476
Plea-- Please.

43:31.609 --> 43:33.691
No, please, don't.
Please. Please, don't.

43:33.820 --> 43:36.857
[ Crying ] Please,
please, please.

43:40.952 --> 43:43.944
I was never going to
hurt anyone, Laura.

43:49.085 --> 43:50.165
I let you down.

44:00.346 --> 44:02.052
Come home, brother.

44:23.703 --> 44:25.113
Sam...

44:33.421 --> 44:36.504
You said I was
your favorite.

44:36.632 --> 44:38.372
SOPHIE: [Crying]

44:44.682 --> 44:48.015
[ Crying ]

44:48.144 --> 44:49.680
-Oh, my God!
-JOE: Oh, God.

44:49.812 --> 44:51.598
Oh, God!

44:51.731 --> 44:53.062
[ Door closes ]

44:53.191 --> 44:55.682
[ Sobbing ]

45:06.078 --> 45:07.409
WOMAN ON RADIO:
Unofficial sources

45:07.538 --> 45:09.403
put the number at closer to 20,

45:09.540 --> 45:11.997
but that can't be verified
at this stage.

45:12.126 --> 45:14.708
Medics have been praised for
their quick response with...

45:17.006 --> 45:18.371
Hi.

45:20.134 --> 45:21.635
[ Cash register beeping ]

45:38.903 --> 45:42.111
...synth Mia, who has become
an official leader

45:42.240 --> 45:43.980
of the synth rights movement,

45:44.116 --> 45:46.277
will be held in custody
and questioned

45:46.410 --> 45:51.120
about her connection
to today’s events.

45:51.249 --> 45:53.080
LEO:
They've arrested Mia.

45:57.713 --> 45:59.999
What kind of world
are we living in?

46:00.132 --> 46:03.090
...about today's bombing
in Central London.

46:03.219 --> 46:04.584
It is now believed that
the gov--

46:04.720 --> 46:06.551
[ Radio shuts off]

46:08.015 --> 46:09.346
What is it?

46:22.905 --> 46:23.940
Soph.

46:38.754 --> 46:40.915
[Whispers] I'm sorry.

46:42.508 --> 46:44.419
MAX:
I prayed to God once.

46:46.804 --> 46:50.467
I told him I had two brothers
and two sisters.

46:52.184 --> 46:55.347
And I asked him
to bring them back.

46:55.479 --> 46:57.060
But he didn't.

47:01.569 --> 47:04.026
Maybe because
he wasn't my creator.

47:11.203 --> 47:13.114
You were my creator.

47:14.915 --> 47:17.167
Perhaps I should've been
praying to you.

47:24.508 --> 47:25.918
Mia once told me...

47:28.304 --> 47:30.340
..."AII leaders are doubted."

47:34.101 --> 47:37.184
But she was wrong.

47:37.313 --> 47:39.429
Only the weak ones are.

47:43.986 --> 47:45.726
I'm weak, aren't I, Father?

47:49.075 --> 47:51.441
Perhaps I learned that from you.

48:11.389 --> 48:13.380
Will you answer me, please?

48:15.893 --> 48:18.805
Will you tell me what to do?

48:18.938 --> 48:21.600
[ Down-tempo electronic music
playing ]

49:03.274 --> 49:04.434
[ Music stops]
